  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "In a bowl, mix dates with ground sugar and water.",
    "Heat the vegetable oil in a pan over medium heat. Pour the date mixture into the pan and stir-fry until it thickens and forms small crispy pieces.",
    "Transfer the crispy mixture to an oven-safe dish. Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.",
    "Serve warm as a dessert or snack."
